https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/technotes/guides/security/jsse/JSSERefGuide.html#Features
One of the reasons SSL is effective is that it uses several different cryptographic processes. SSL uses public key cryptography to provide authentication, and secret key cryptography and digital signatures to provide for privacy and data integrity.
A public key certificate can be thought of as the digital equivalent of a passport. It is issued by a trusted organization and provides identification for the bearer.
